# HandoverKey Project Rules

## Architecture

Turborepo monorepo with npm workspaces. Two apps, three shared packages:

- `apps/api` -- Express 5 REST API (Node 22, TypeScript)
- `apps/web` -- React 19 SPA (Vite, Tailwind CSS)
- `packages/crypto` -- AES-256-GCM, PBKDF2, Shamir's Secret Sharing (Web Crypto API)
- `packages/database` -- Kysely + PostgreSQL repositories
- `packages/shared` -- Cross-package types, constants, validation

### Dependency Direction

```
apps/api → packages/database, packages/crypto, packages/shared
apps/web → packages/shared (indirectly via API responses)
packages/shared → packages/crypto
packages/database → (standalone)
packages/crypto → (standalone)
```

Never introduce circular dependencies between packages.

## API Conventions

- All routes under `/api/v1/` prefix
- Pattern: `routes/ → controllers/ → services/ → repositories/`
- Controllers handle HTTP; services handle business logic; repositories handle data
- Always use `next(error)` in controllers -- never `res.status(500).json()` directly
- Always use the Pino `logger` from `src/config/logger.ts` -- never `console.log/error/warn`
- Wrap async route handlers with `asyncHandler` or catch and call `next(error)`
- Validate requests with Zod schemas in `src/validation/schemas/`

## Error Handling

- Throw typed errors from `apps/api/src/errors/index.ts` (AppError hierarchy)
- The global `errorHandler` middleware formats all errors consistently
- Operational errors (4xx) log at `warn`; non-operational (5xx) log at `error`
- Never expose internal error details in production responses
- Database `NotFoundError` (from `@handoverkey/database`) is auto-mapped to HTTP 404 by the error handler
- Other `DatabaseError` subclasses are auto-mapped to HTTP 500
- `ValidationError` exists separately in `packages/crypto` (crypto layer) and `apps/api/src/errors` (HTTP layer) -- this is intentional since they serve different abstraction layers

## Security Constraints

- Never hardcode secrets or provide fallback values for JWT_SECRET, DB passwords, etc.
- Use environment variable validation at startup -- fail fast if required vars are missing
- CORS must use an explicit origin allowlist, not `callback(null, true)`
- Tokens must be stored in httpOnly cookies, not localStorage
- All admin routes must enforce role-based authorization
- Body parser limit should be <=5MB for JSON endpoints

## Frontend Conventions

- Pages in `src/pages/`, reusable components in `src/components/`
- Auth state via `AuthContext`, toast notifications via `ToastContext`
- API calls through the axios instance in `src/services/api.ts`
- Client-side encryption via `src/services/encryption.ts`
- All protected routes wrapped in `ProtectedRoute`

## Testing

- API: Jest 30 with integration tests against real PostgreSQL
- Web: Vitest with @testing-library/react
- Packages: Jest 30 with ESM preset
- Crypto package enforces 80% coverage threshold
- Never commit placeholder tests (empty `it("works")` blocks)
- Critical flows (auth, vault CRUD, handover) must have integration tests

## File Naming

- Kebab-case for all files: `vault-controller.ts`, `auth-routes.ts`
- Test files: `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx`, colocated in `__tests__/`
- SQL migrations: descriptive names in `src/database/schema/`

## Git & CI

- Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `build:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `refactor:`
- PR pipeline runs lint, build, migrate, test against PostgreSQL 16 + Redis 7
- Dependabot manages npm (weekly) and GitHub Actions (monthly)
